The paper focuses on the design and prototyping of privacy-preserving interventions for voice assistants, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and cybersecurity (CYBER) aspects. The study also involves exploring the trade-offs among utility, privacy, and usability, which falls under the categories of security and privacy (CR), social and information networks (SI), and software engineering (SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC, followed by cs.CYBER, cs.CR, cs.SI, and cs.SD.
